* [Tesla investigated over 'phantom braking' problem](https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-60432351)

  This article talks about the US government's recent investigations of Tesla, after it received hundreds of 
  complaints regarding some of the Tesla models unexpectedly applying brakes and decelerating without giving
  warnings to the driver. This incident resulted in several near-miss collisions; however, there were no 
  injuries and/or casualties that were caused from the incident. According to the article, the incident is
  at its very before stage before Tesla can officially call for a recall for the models involved in this 
  incident. As of today, the investigation is continued and no conclusion has been made. 
  
